data.title: windows tmp.exe errors and malicious web blocking
data.meta_description: Well, I got hit somehow - despite having Avast and Malwarebytes professional. 1) At startup I get: Svr32 (RegLGdrvNetwork8.dll failed to load)2) Then I get repeated errors for missing temp exe files in ProgramData/Microsoft/Secure/Icons/temp/tmpSomeNumber.exeHowever, Avast also repeatedly catches...
data.text:
Here's the FRST log - I tried the others (GMER and TDSSKiller) as well, but evidently they need more running to work - I got an error stating that the subsystem needed to support the image type wasn't present.
